title: Grateful Dead Live at Roosevelt Stadium on 1974-08-06
description:
Set 1

Bertha, Mexicali Blues, Don't Ease Me In, Beat It On Down The Line, Sugaree, Jack Straw, Eyes Of The World, Promised Land, Deal, Playin' In The Band-> Scarlet Begonias-> Playin' In The Band

Set 2

Phil & Ned*, Uncle John's Band, Black Peter, El Paso, Loose Lucy, Big River, Ship of Fools, Me & My Uncle, Row Jimmy, Sugar Magnolia-> He's Gone-> Truckin'-> Drums-> Spanish Jam-> The Other One-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Sunshine Daydream, E: U.S. Blues

*Phil & Ned Between sets.

reviews.review_text: Put the Eyes on, puff something solventless, and relax This show is amazing, big big thanks to aLL involved in getting out there to the listeners.

Yessum last one before they moved off to EUR
jamming

Wall of Sound These audience recordings do a much better job at showcasing the famed Wall of Sound. There's a couple soundboards of this show and they sound fantastic. Like every early seventies boot, I recommend listening to different sources. Sometimes you'll find a gem that has that special something that tickles the ear, sometimes you'll wonder why the tapes didn't get thrown in the bin... But when you find a special tape it makes it all worthwhile
.
